title: Perth suburb trapped beneath dust cloud from development | 7NEWS
description: Residents in Huntingdale, Perth's southeast, are experiencing severe dust and silt pollution blowing from the nearby Parkside Estate housing development. Homes, pools and backyards are covered in layers of dirt that sticks to surfaces and requires constant water use to clean. Health experts warn that invisible airborne particles pose the greatest health risks, while residents fear conditions will worsen as stage three of the development proceeds with further bushland clearing.
